thread.title: Apple takes the wraps off 32GB and 128GB models of the iPhone SE
thread.title_full: Apple takes the wraps off 32GB and 128GB models of the iPhone SE

author: Josh Levenson
title: Apple takes the wraps off 32GB and 128GB models of the iPhone SE
text:
Apple has today added two new variants of the iPhone SE to its online store — a 32GB and 128GB model. Both units are set to go on sale this Friday, March 24 alongside the iPad and iPhone 7 (Product)RED Special Edition and will be priced at $399 and $499, respectively.
The new storage sizes will replace the 16GB and 64GB variants that were introduced last year. The firm’s already removed the original versions from its online store, so those still hoping to pick one up (we’re not sure why you’d want to, either) have no choice but to resort to third-party channels, like Amazon and eBay.
The new models sport the same specs As you’d expect, the Apple hasn’t made any other tweaks to the internals of the iPhone SE. It still lacks a 3D Touch display and sports a 1.84GHz dual-core A9 chip (on par with the iPhone 6S), a 12MP rear-facing camera, a 1.2MP selfie shooter and a 1,624mAh non-removable battery.
